{"body": "That would work, with the implicit assumption that running `super(&block)` is semantically equivalent to:\r\n\r\n```ruby\r\nsuper { |x| x }.tap { |railties| railties.each(&block) }\r\n```\r\ni.e. it runs the given block over exactly the same elements as its return value, and in the same order.\r\n\r\nAnother alternative is to replace `super { |x| x }` with just a call to `plugins`\r\n", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/comments/1383593", "created_at": "2011-06-16T19:22:51Z", "html_url": "https://github.com/rails/rails/pull/1458#issuecomment-1383593", "updated_at": "2011-06-16T19:22:51Z", "repo": "rails", "issue_id": 1458, "user": {"following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jhtwong/following{/other_user}", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jhtwong/events{/privacy}", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jhtwong/orgs", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jhtwong", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jhtwong/gists{/gist_id}", "html_url": "https://github.com/jhtwong", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jhtwong/subscriptions", "avatar_url": "https://1.gravatar.com/avatar/cbac8261deee7dc43c44e2fd62af9c14?d=https%3A%2F%2Fidenticons.github.com%2F1916dd4db010a27d419d07a8c838edb2.png", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jhtwong/repos", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jhtwong/received_events", "gravatar_id": "cbac8261deee7dc43c44e2fd62af9c14", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jhtwong/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "login": "jhtwong", "type": "User", "id": 826393, "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/jhtwong/followers"}, "owner": "rails", "_id": {"$oid": "5238510bbd3543c15101173a"}, "id": 1383593, "issue_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rails/rails/issues/1458"}
